Stop by around noon and again at sundown for tasty treats, groovy beats, and some dance in your pants.
name: Garden, The

description: The Hen House Presents: Speed Dating, Twerk Shops, and a Tang Bang Block Party. Come visit the Hen Den where you might meet the love of your life, learn the greatest dance move, and enjoy tasty tang bangs with new friends.
name: Hen House, The

description: A buzzing mass of madness from the East descends upon the desert, full of burning light and energy. Is the Hive full of honey, or stings? Bathe in our glow, and discover!
name: The Hive

description:
Come to the Hookah Lounge and enjoy our flavored tobaccos, coffee, and wide selection of teas. Our Moroccan style lounge serves up shisha filtered through juice and water every night. The plush seating, soft carpeting, and great people make this the ultimate Burning Man chill-out zone. If you have a favorite molasses based tobacco, you are welcome to bring it and share* with others. Karaoke sundown to midnight.

* Please respect: no illegal drugs.
name: Hookah Lounge, The

description: Come create art while enjoying an ice cold glass of lemonade!
name: Lemonade Stand, The

description: What could be more lost than a Penguin in the desert? Drop in to our hospitality oasis where we offer comforts such as shade, couches, wine, lemonade, chocolate, snow cones, friendly people, and live entertainment.  Day or night, get up on stage for asshole theatre, watch some bands, dance to DJs or take a workshop. Join us as we navigate surpirses all week!  Or just sit and we will engage you in conversation as you watch the playa float by.
name: Lost Penguin, The

description: The Monks of Funk are here to guide you to nirvana through music and dance. Join us for one of our scheduled sermons or just drop in to our Dance Church for some meditation, rejuvenation, and/or hip gyration!
name: Monks of Funk, The

description: The Phage is an homage to the vast dark ecology whose foment gave birth to Earth's living diversity. These ubiquitous viral life forms evolve faster than any other life on earth. In their furious co-optive radiations they have acted as the vital genetic pollinators that wove long-separated lines of cellular life into resplendent new threads -- the phage are the needles of life's tapestry. Beware if you encounter us: memetic biohazards lie ahead.
hometown: San Francisco, Los Angeles, NYC, CA, NY
name: Phage, The

hometown: Houston, New York & Melbourne, Texas, New York & Victoria
name: Possible Project, The

description: Your friendly, local, international watering hole and second home on the playa returns for a fifth year. Stop by to wet your whistle, just take care not to trip over folks passed out on the floor. If you want a quiet pint be sure to pop in before sunset, after which it gets slightly raucous.  If you've had enough of bars then give a pub a go. Stop by for much libations and games including, new for 2014... Battle Shots.
name: Rising Arms, The

description: The Steam Bath Project makes the mundane magical! The simple act of “cleansing” becomes part of an age-old  ritual tradition embracing the possibility of transformation. We invite you into the geodesic dome where you can relax on the wooden benches as boiling water produces steam with negative ions that fill the space. Negative ions are known to create an overall feeling of wellness, similar to the air after a summer thunderstorm.
name: Steam Bath Project, The

description: The Sunset trip is the home base of 4 Los Angeles based camps: Camp Charlie, The Dirty Beetles, Transmorphagon, and the Tasty Noodles. Stop by in the afternoon for craft beer from the Noodle Craft Beer Bar and come back at night for the Capital Reckers Main Stage for live music and DJs. We'll also be featuring a red carpet, walk of shame, the unicorn branding station, electric swing set, giant light bright, post card photo station, and more.
name: The Sunset Trip

description: A different theme every day with activities and tasty libations to match
name: Theme Camp Theme Camp

description: Including but never limited to: swings! hammocks! pendulums! people! We’re hosting events on dome construction and social grooming (adults only), and we welcome you to step under our shade any time of day or enjoy our camp fire at night.
name: Things That Swing

description: Bullshit! is the new awesome and this camp is full of it!  We are hosting Salsa Dance workshops/parties throughout the week; also stop by anytime to turn your bike into a raging bull so that you can stampede with us through the streets of Black Rock city during the 4th annual Running of the Bulls, plus Asshole Karaoke, Wheel of Consequences, Bullshit Games and much more.  So check the playa schedule, because This Camp is Bullshit!
hometown: Los Angeles and San Fransico, California
name: This Camp is Bullshit

description:
A sound camp for things that go THUMP in the night.  A stimulating communal dance party where intimacy isn't sacrificed for sound.
http://soundcloud.com/thumpercamp
name: Thumper

description: A time travel agency and resource center for the temporally dislocated. Come enjoy games, drinks, and performances from the past, present and future!
name: Time Colony

description: The nexus of time has opened and heroes from throughout the ages have gathered together for great justice.Come share your experiences as a time traveler or get some tips from the pros on how to keep the time line intact. Join us for our time travel party on Thursday from 4-10pm! Where we'll travel to a different time period every hour.
name: Time Ninja Syndicate

description: Lost? Confused? Runny nose? Don't know what to go do next? Camp Tissue and a Plan is dedicated to making sure no burner wanders the playa without a clear plan and a clean tissue. 'Cause all you really need is a tissue and a plan..
name: Tissue and a Plan

description: Join these high mountain dwellers in their desert caravan.  Sit a spell in our open shade and enjoy the Middle Eastern Bazaar environment.
name: Titicaca

description: If you'd like to learn a DUTTCH or practice a LATCH, come on by the RANCH and train with the best. After that, hang at the PATCH for delicious pancakes. a workshop, handcrafted necklaces, BUNCHES of titties, and/or random performances of a slightly epic nature. RATS RATCH!!
name: TITTIES N PANCAKES LOW FILL RANCH

description: ToneAge - Karavantastique! returns for its lucky number 7th year on the playa and welcomes young and old, Virgin or Burnior Citizen to come by for a cup of coffee in the morning, music (and shade!) in the afternoon, fire after sunset, and our Oasis party WED night! We are a bunch of SFer's, Denverites, Vancouverians, and SoCalistas - and wherever you are from, you're welcome!
hometown: Primarily, SF, Denver, Vancouver, CA, CO, BC
name: ToneAge - Karavantastique!

description: Once again we scour the absolute blackened foulest depths of the darkest  vicious hollows to dredge from within the most brutal undeniable might what is all things Metal! Join us again to raise fist and fury, scream rage and power, hold court on high while we celebrate the immensity, the strength, the beauty of the most powerful musical culture ever created!! \m/
name: Totem Wolf!!!

description: Totenkitten is a fascist demagoguery devoted to crushing all opposition and imposing our will on the masses; initially conceived as a reaction to the decadent weakness of other organizations, Totenkitten quickly took on a life of its own.
hometown: Boston and Toronto, Massachusetts and Ontario
name: Totenkitten

description: Looking for the perfect pair of shades to go with that costume?  Or maybe you forgot, lost, ate, misplaced, broke yours… Come on over to Trader Shady's sunglass exchange camp to swap stories and sunnies on your way out to the playa fun.
name: Trader Shady's

description: TRANSMORPHAGON - Within the Sunset Trip Village, TGon will bring you the best of House & Live music, and an appropriate dose of fun!  Come hang under the Transporter, and be transported to a more inclusive and fun world!
name: Transmorphagon

description: The Witch's Hat returns, along with some special surprises. Pleasant or not? You be the judge.
hometown: Various hick towns of the earth, California, Colorado, New York
name: Trashistan

description: Ever have a treehouse when you were a kid?  Come play at The Treehouse and join us for a drink at the cards against humanity bar, a game of charades (with costumes!) or an improv class.
name: The Treehouse

description:
This is the public page for camp Trifucta at Burning Man! Like this page to stay up to date with event's and projects we are producing. We are a large community of friends looking to give back to our community through art and music )'(

https://www.facebook.com/Trifucta
name: Trifucta

description: A verdant home alive with the warmth of aloha!  Castaways welcomed to paddle up to the tiki lights and toast the night with a Mai Thai.
name: Tropical Treehouse

description: A welcome respite along the dusty silk route featuring Playa Fashion Makeovers, Live Music, Snow Cones, Wordsmithing, advice, and sweet satisfaction.
name: TSUNAMI CAMP

description: This is your chance to show off your under-appreciated talents on our custom built stage for a spaghetti dinner! Terrible face/tramp stamp painting, hairy lap dances, drunk yoga, and constant heckling are also our specialties.
name: Twilight Spaghetti Theatre

description: Welcome to Twin Freaks!  Enter our Freaky world of doppelgangers, mystery, talking logs, strange artifacts, and the best damn cup of coffee on the Playa.  The owls are not what they seem...
hometown: Bay Area/All over the Universe!, CA
name: Twin Freaks

description: Best weddings on the playa, Unofficial Playa Civil Unions (including rings/certificate), Black Rock Temporary Divorce, Annulments, legal weddings by prior arrangement.  Be sure to experience our interactive elwire sculpture!
name: Two Lanterns

description: Got questions about your two-stroke engine? Maybe you just like to rev up your engine and make a lot of noise? Come on down to Two-Stroke Transit to talk to us. While here, you can find out how to prevent playa damage from dripping oil while improving your engine's performance.
name: Two-Stroke Transit

description: “Uplifting Soul Massages” - a powerful healing process that assists in connecting to our Authentic Self.  This process releases old stuck energies of fear, sadness and resentments and creates space for Self-love as well as a loving bond between the participants.
hometown: Los Angeles and New York City, California and New York
name: U See Me

description: UFO Response Team will be the one stop shop to report UFO/Alien sightings in Black Rock City!
name: UFO Response Team

description: Uhuru has the voodoo for what you do. Join us to explore curiosity, wonder, and adventure.
name: Uhuru

description: O illustrious merchants of the flesh and pillagers of the wealth of man. Our glorious master, Uli Baba, he who is magnificent and just, he who rules with the wisdom of Solomon and the might of Saladin, commands your presence at his slave auctions, belly dance competition & workshops.  http://www.meetup.com/Uli-Babas/
name: Uli Baba and the Horny Thieves

description: The end is nigh! Eschatological salons (readings, discussion and dialectic) commence at 2pm Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday. Come prepared to probe the transcendental depths of End Times concepts in variety of cultural, religious and literary disciplines, from the four horsemen of the apocalypse, to Ragnarök, to Elliot’s Wasteland, to visions of a technological singularity. Sip the ambrosia of the Twilight of the Gods (the official libation of our Ultimate Celebration) while you contemplate your own ultimate destination.
hometown: San Francisco, New York City, CA, NY
name: Ultimate Celebration

description: Universe University, contemporary classroom/carnival. Complete with playground, rec center, cafeteria, and lounge. Come back to your roots.. and win some prizes too!
name: Universe University

description: The slap of skin. The crack of flesh. The bang of bodies. What better way to celebrate your amusement, joy, or just plain agreement then the abrupt collision of two hands. The high five… or in our case, unnecessarily high five. Come by and try your luck at the Unnecessarily High Five. Can you hit our highest five? We’re waiting for someone who can. Bring friends, bring your robot helper, bring a trampoline and fling yourself into the history books.
hometown: Alameda, CA / New York, NY, CA
name: Unnecessarily High Five

description: The V-SPoT is Burning Man’s official Volunteer Headquarters in Black Rock City. Where different projects come to seek Volunteers and where Burners come to find out how to help. Our friendly Volunteer Experts are here to answer your questions and help you find your “special place” on the Playa.
name: V-Spot

description: As vagabonds and tagalongs, we strive to attract, include, and discover all the other vagabonds and tag-alongs out there. We come from all corners of the US and even Australia, brought together by our love for radical expression and inclusion, with a little help from the wonderful world wide web.
name: Vagabonds & Tagalongs

description: Valhalla is a new camp built by veteran burners from several camps. We want to provide a nighttime community space, and a seed for a particular flavor of communal adventure and questing.
name: Valhalla

description:
Vamp Camp. We only come out at night! (Unless we wake up early.)
Vamp juice, burn barrel, music and Vamp Stamp if deserving!
No Schedules, no commitments. If you are here, you are on time.
Find us on facebook
name: Vamp Camp

description: An interactive environment to discuss sustainable farming, healthy diets, local food sourcing and global views on the future of meat production advantages & disadvantages.  It's also a fun place with the "Wheel O Meat" and lively discussions and drinks.
name: Vegan Nightmare Camp

description: A camp focus Spreading Burning Man Culture throughout Latin America.
name: VIDA

description: Nightly video projection on our two big screens. Body painting, airbrushing and spray paint art every afternoon in our dome. Come by and cool off in our mister!  Record a message for your "Former Virgin" then watch it later on our screens. Play Playa Jeopardy on Wednesday Night. Live Rocky Horror Picture Show on Friday Night. Contact us if you have an original video you'd like to show. Located in Snowflake Village.
name: Videogasm

description: If you are hot, thirsty, and decaffeinated while on the playa then come to VICE for refreshing, hand-made Vietnamese Iced Coffee, afternoons from 2 to 4pm.  Learn to walk on Stilts, dance with Flags, or create Perler Bead keepsakes at one of our interactive workshops at VICE - a friendly, diverse camp who wants to see YOU in line for coffee!
hometown: Many – Bay Area, LA Area, Albuquerque, Washington DC, Seattle, Salt Lake City, etc., CA, DC, NM, UT, WA
name: Vietnamese Iced Coffee Experience

description: Vines Without Borders is a global wine bar and lounge inviting guests and offering wines from around the world. Each night starting at sunset a different wine region will be celebrated in our cool LED illuminated venue furnished with vintage couches and chairs and a long back-lit bar.
name: Vines Without Borders

description: Are you in awe of the hottie hoopers on the Playa? Come by Virgin Hooper Camp and we will teach you how to hula hoop. We can teach anyone in 10 minutes or less!
name: Virgin Hooper Camp

description: Exercise your demons - shoot voodoo dolls and shrunken heads to win glow cups emblazoned with Voodoo 2013 camp logo. Hosted by the best collection of French voodoo priestesses and their zombie slaves to cheer and award you prizes and treats.
name: Voodoo Shooting Gallery

description: Skateboarding and rock and roll drenched in whiskey. Come to the camp that singlehandedly defends BRC against constant dubstep onslaughts. Aint no fuckin' accident we're Voted Best Camp.
name: Voted Best Camp

description: Come to Vulcantown and experience flow in all of it's glory. We will be playing constantly and invite everyone to come join in the fun.
name: Vulcantown

description: VW Bus Caravaners, stop and camp with the VW Bus Caravansary at Black Rock City. Stay and participate with us at the great Burning Man Caravansary, before continuing on your paths across the wilderness of Nevada and places beyond, VW Bus Camp, where camaraderie and the spirit of Burning Man has lived on now for 17 Burns.
name: VW Bus Camp

description: We Will Stamp You! Come on by and have a good time. Small camp to come chill and relax get stamped and heckle people, various shenanigans and vulgar mouths will take place here.
name: Walkover

description: Our Camp is an oasis on the playa for the Wandering Burner who happens upon our camp and finds HUGS, Gin/Tonic, and Hot Dogs,  Come by every afternoon for our playa hot dog feed, have a gin/tonic and enjoy the shade, great company and music.
name: Wanderer's Camp

description: If you Want It! but can't find it here, then we're probably Nawt It.
name: Want It!

description: Warp Zone, purveyors of Aggressive Hospitality since 2010, are delighted to return home to Black Rock City for another beautiful year. Come warm up in the wee hours with tea next to the Hexaheart fire, or stop by during the day for an afternoon workshop, or just to say hi!
name: Warp Zone

description: The Wasabi Kisses theme camp seeks to create a space were sexuality and gender identity are respected and where queer, trans*, genderqueer, and gender variant folks can get their kink on with a focus on consent, safer spaces, and queer/trans* visibility.
name: Wasabi Kisses

description: Join us atop Stoop’s Stoop to catch a desert sunset, or grab the megaphone and heckle our neighbors - just watch your bottom when you catch the zip-line back down. We're back again for another round of mistakes!
name: Well Made Mistakes

description: Crank, Crank, Crank.  Camp WeScream invites the community to participate NOW in the creation of ice cream using 3 modern 6 quart wooden ice cream makers. We will ask the community to Scream for their ice cream and then crank away.
name: WeScream

description: A forgotten paradise to soothe the weary adventurer, or a lawless land of risk & reward? We are both.  A yin and a yang.  An amalgamation of two elements, each playing off the other.  Village now featuring prodigal Wet Dreams and Liminal Spaces!
name: Wet Dreams

description: The WetSpot Bar & Faceplant Lounge: Welcome to the best place on the playa to enjoy a home crafted beer while relaxing in our unique lounge. WetSpot is about making new friends in an open to all setting while engaging in musings around one of our favorite pastimes: brewing beer. Our crew includes homebrewers and non-homebrewers alike and provides an inviting atmosphere to sample and learn about the art and science of brewing beer as well as just having fun.
name: Wetspot

description: Helping our community members keep their cargo in good repair! We will instruct and assist people on useful playa fixes using duct tape in innovative and creative ways to repair, strengthen and create!
name: What Would Duck Tape Do?

description: Have you ever experienced the juicy perfection of eating a pickle on the playa? Come visit us so we can ask What Would You Do For a Pickle?
name: What Would You Do For A Pickle?

description:
The Dojo is the place of the way, here, there and everywhere...
finders, seekers, we are the way.
name: Where is the Dojo

description: Where's My Pants? Camp is the best camp EVAR!  Come in your pants and play with our burningman lego set, sit on our double-decker couch, and let's celebrate how AWESOME everything is!  If you lost your pants (it happens!), we'll find a pair for you.
name: Where's My Pants? Camp

description: Calling all aerialists, we'll be bringing it with a giant tripod for silk and lyra performances, workshops and skill shares.  Take a load off in the shade of our circus tent or climb up to the high bar on top of our school bus for spectacular views of the playa and the performers.
name: Whisker Biscuit

description: Simply put, we are a Whiskey camp with a small habitual yoga problem. Join our always popular shaded bar stocked with the many flavors of alluring liquids. Enjoy the conversation, events, aerial acrobatic performances, vinyl music and various workshops (Yoga, Juggling, Dancing, Hooping, etc.) throughout the week. Continuing with our previous theme, we hope to continue to bring more new and creative concepts to the community.
name: Whiskey and Dust

description: With massive steel rising from the playa, we are hosting some of our favorite friends from around the globe for you, our family and friends.
name: White Ocean

description:
Were your friendly Neighborhood dive bar. We have no set schedule so If the bar stools are down and/or musics on, come join us for a drink or some shine if we haven't already drank it all.

Bring your own cup to pimp out, and enjoy the shade on comfy couches and have fun playing a variety of bar games.
name: White Trash Superstars

description: Come to Camp WhoofARTed?! (It was me!) and Get The F*%$ Out! for fun, libations, food, libations, frolicking, libations, bacon, libations, games, libations, art, libations, and general merriment (and libations)! Visit our Hydration Station and spend time in our chill living room - the perfect place to enjoy some shade, friends, dust, and, of course, libations! Look for our bacon and bloody mary events, random late-night foods, photos, and more!
hometown: Las Vegas, Seattle, Melbourne, Nevada, Washington, Victoria
name: WhoofARTed?! & Get the F*%$ Out!

description: This is the place where fairy-tale world is turned upside-down and awaits for you to jump in! We welcome burners for participation in familiar stories slipped from the pages of familiar chilhood books that meet adult world. Are you still a Virgin? Come to WICKEDLAND and trust yourself into gentle hands of expierienced burner for a day or a week, or... maybe a lifetime? Are you an old-timer BM-champ? Then help a newcomers and Adopt-A-Virgin here!
name: WickedLand

description: Wiener Zoo! Where neighbors and friends can stop by for a  hotdog or some cocktail weenies. Daily from 3-6.
name: Wiener Zoo

description: Everyone’s a winner; you get chicken dinner. Want some wings and beer? You can find them here!
name: Winner Winner Chicken Dinner

description: Come visit us at Wish Maker!  From 3pm-6pm daily.  We provide you with burnable articles and the tools to fashion your own meaningful tribute or object of devotion.  Our talented table dwellers will help you create something that is worthy of its meaning to you, friend.  Our wishing ribbons will be available always for your wishes leave them on our wall and we will deliver to the temple for you at sunrise on Sunday before the burn.  Please join us!
name: Wish Maker

description: we wish you were here to join us in our photo project; come by any time for your pic.
name: Wish U Were Here Camp

description: WMICC brings nearly one ton of delicious organic produce to the people of Black Rock City. Come for the juicy goodness and stay for the delightful experience.
name: WMICC Organic Fruit & Veggie Bar

description: Womp Camp is a group of fun loving Canadian and International Burners dedicated to fun, shenanigans, laughter, great music, sustainability, and community. A headquarters for a mobile fun squad and a community experience that will extend far beyond the Playa, come say hi :)
name: Womp Camp

description: Wonder Camp is a place where you can bring your broken project, mutant vehicle, heart, etc......or we will come to you! Complete mobile repair for the broken Burner.
name: Wonder Camp

description: So Wrong. Sooo Phil.
name: Wrongtown & [Phil in the Blank]

description: Our dome contains a participant driven, high kinetic energy play space. Every action has it's reaction: every motion has it's emotion.
name: Yabba Dabba DoMe

description: The Yellow Bike Shop is dedicated to servicing ONLY the community yellow bike fleet.
name: Yellow Bikes

description: Camp "Yes, &" is a group of friends from Seattle (and often further afield).  The phrase "Yes, &" is borrowed from Improv, and we have made it our own, to indicate that no matter what the idea is... we're in.
name: Yes, And

description: Your Mom's camp - we do what mom's do - sew your stuff (costume and minor tent repair), listen to you, support you, and make you feel at home.
name: Your Mom's

description: Live interactive performance oriented camp uniting burners through laughter, curiosity, and consciousness.  Mobile group performances, social experiments, storytelling, workshops and home of The Yum Cart...people leave with a smile and often come back for seconds.
name: Yummy RUMInations

description: Not necessarily the future the way it will be; the future the way it should to be...shiny!!  Home of a radio listening tea lounge and some shiny, happy people.
name: Yurtopia

description: Come Dance and Brush your Teeth!
name: Zen as Fuck

description: The Zendo Project will return to the playa this year to offer a tranquil space and compassionate care for individuals seeking psychological support on the playa. Trained volunteers will be available around the clock inside our open-air yurt-like structure and bedouin-style tea house.
name: Zendo Project

description: We like to get down AND get up, depending on the time of day.
name: Zoodiac Academy

description: Anything can happen in Black Rock City, and nobody knows this better than the Man himself.  In 2014, he looks down at the Esplanade and sees something especially peculiar.  It’s a rare phenomenon, only ever seen in the ocean’s deep volcanic fissures and other unfathomable places.  Here, nearly a mile above the ocean, fire under the sea illuminates the high desert.  Come by for our music, lights, dancing, fire lessons, open spin, fire baseball, fire dodge ball, and playground.
name: !Zoom!

description: Come hang with the animals at the Zooniverse!
name: Zooniverse

description: Techno and Tech house stage with live performances and art.
name: Zuvuya Tribe

description: As you enter our friendly fort you will find a full red round rocking chair that will take you on a up-side-down trip if you choose to do so. You will also a selection of robots that Burners can remote control to fight each other within the safely enclosed BattleBot arena. By hosting tournaments on a daily basis we hope to reach many eager minds and allow the robots and competitors to morph throughout the week. In addition to robots, our camp also features a friendly competition in a game of laser tag. We hope that Burners will join our journey of interactive technology and emerge with a rejuvenated view of our world.
name: Phasmantis Apparatus

description: Glitter and Rust will have a Badminton court, a cornhole set, and a photo-op mural. Bring your camera and/or your best game face. We are a multiethnic chill group willing to hang out, have deep philosophical discussions, be your adversary at a game, or just smile and wave as you pass by.
name: Glitter and Rust

description: Home of the infamous Lamplighter Bar. Where we host a daily recruitment party from 3pm - 5pm each day, but are open 22 hours a day. Come stop by and enjoy our shade, grab a drink and stick around to volunteer to help us light the city.
name: Lamplighter Village

description: Flying Falafels is a camp consists of Israeli And American burners together. We are intending on serving hot "Falafel" balls every day around lunch time with some nice mellow Mediterranean music playing in the background , with a peak event of a "falafel party " on Friday 2 pm-until the evening.
name: Flying Falafels

description: Ranger Outpost
name: Ranger Outpost Tokyo

description: Ranger HQ
name: Ranger Headquarters

description: Ranger Outpost Berlin
name: Ranger Outpost Berlin

description: Visit Census Lab to learn about the Black Rock City Census, check out survey data on participants from prior year Burns, and make an entry in the Analog Census.
name: Census Lab

description: Staff Camp for Rangers
name: Ranger Outpost Moscow

description: Gypsy Flower Power camp a band of Gypsies hailing from 10 countries & 13 states celebrating the Flower Power Era Summer of Love spreading the Burner culture and Love worldwide
name: Gypsy Flower Power International

description: Wide Awake Oasis Bar
name: Wide Awake Oasis Bar

description:
Giant lite Brite.  Playagoers will stumble across this giant
rendering of their favorite childhood toy that invites them to interact
and create spontaneous light sculptures that express their thoughts and
ideas in the moment.
name: Light Brite

description: Bringing together "self & other" in unique and interesting ways. Come with another, or be prepared to meet one.
Are you telling me that you built a time machine... out of a DeLorean?
name: 1.21 Gigawatts

description: 11 Forward: its like 10 Forward, the bar from The USS Enterprise, but this one goes to eleven. We like to mix our cultural references like we mix our cocktails, randomly.
name: 11 Forward

description: We are your ultimate Sundowner! Come enjoy a top-shelf, ice-cold gin & tonic in our famously lush desert oasis bar, cool down with the new misting system, and get your groove on to quality down tempo, soul, funk, disco & house. You won't want to miss Electro-Swing Wednesday with its sultry Burlesque Show – or taking a spin on our rideable giraffe, Special Ed! It’s all happening Monday - Saturday, 3.30pm - 6.30pm.
name: 7 Deadly Gins

description:
Come Embrace the Heat as the Playa's Friendliest Little Slice of Hell returns for the 14th straight year!
Daytime brings what Sinners need - shade, chill music and slushy drinks.
But NIGHT brings what Sinners want - Flaming Libations and the ever popular WHEEL of SINS! 
Our highly skilled and dedicated staff will happily deliver absolution & encouragement with a FIRM hand! 
So come earn your "Get Out of HELL Free" card and remember to Start your SINS at 7!
name: 7 Sins Lounge

description: A pirate bohemia where merrymaking, gypsy lounging, dancing rhythms and mischief run aground.  Beware, it is futile to resist the 7 Siren’s call!
name: 7 Sirens Cove

description: Each of us has 9 Energy Centers in our bodies, one of which is more active than the others – called the Active Energy. Knowing your Active Energy or Superpower gives you physical access to your spiritual nature. Sober please!
name: 9 Energies

description: The dead horse is scarce, and we continue to beat it. Come by and sit in the desert in A Camp With No Name, where you will be told that buttered popcorn is a perfectly fantastic snow cone flavor – why would you think otherwise? (Don’t worry – there are “normal” flavors.) Look for us carting around chai or tidying up the playa with our vacuum cleaner.
name: A Camp with No Name (ACWNN)

description:
Come and visit a Cosmic Carnival and may your body never miss a beat to the rhythm of this world.
Here at Camp Cosmic Carnival music and artistic expression is encouraged and during daylight hours our two sides stages will be available to anyone who wishes to play. During dusk and evening hours we will host art, fire dancers, fire performers, live bands and of course carnival rides, games and a laser light show. From 8 a.m. to 12 p.m. and 2 p.m. to 5 p.m. we will be hosting a kids camp for any children, accompanied by their guardian or parents, to enjoy the rides, games and jam out on the karaoke stage. So come on down and join us at cosmic carnival and let our vision lift you to the stars.
name: A Cosmic Carnivale

description: SIT HAPPENS HERE 24x7. Shady chairs & lounges: refresh, rest, meet Burners. Enjoy iced water, healthy snax, lots of activities & WiFi.
name: A Shack of Sit

description: Breathe easy with the Maskman’s quality N95 dust masks with their psychedelic Burning Man logo.
name: A-Playa Mask

description: Need a tickle? We'll be bringing our tickle trunk of costumes galore; adorn, choose, trade, and pose! We will take your photo (if u would like) to admire yourself once you leave playa of your amazing outfits. Need a disguise for the day or week? We've got ya covered! Come join us from 1pm-5pm every day; relax and get fabulous, and don't forget to STRIKE THAT POSE!
name: A-TickleTrunkTastic Camp

description: Welcome to Camp Above the Limit's Crystal Medina! Enter the domed arch to find Turkish coffee, spirits, chill spaces, lights, music, aromas, and conversations that will take you from the shifting sands of the desert to the corridors of your own psyche. Or just kick back in the pillows and have a nap. On the other side of the Medina, come help us rock the casbah with the Afterburner Lounge, its firepit, and the Black Rock Air Force's own F-15.
name: Above The Limit

description: ABR is a tight-knit group of weird people whose values stem from a strong foundation of cooperative living, self-reliance, and responsibility. Our camp encourages playfulness, creativity, and exploration, and provides a casual social space for burners old and new alike.
name: ABR: Apt But Random

description: Calling all sinners!  Step into our street-front confessional and tell it to someone who gives a shit- our resident priests and priestesses are standing by to prescribe your personalized atonement regiment.  Stay for holy water at our bar: IPFuckinA is back along with a special new brew!  The dusty, thirsty masses will be served every afternoon until the kegs are blown.
name: AbsoFuckinLution

description: Abstininthe is the friendly bar on the playa, providing our special drink to the thirsty of BRC since the last millennium. Come try our many flavors and enjoy the music, ambiance and conversation of our neighborhood bar.
name: Abstininthe

description: Welcome to the Academy of Arts and Sciences. We have interactive classes teaching burners about science that can be used to create art, as well as art that makes science real. We strive to balance the left/right brain dichotomy with a range of activities to meet our fellow Burners’ diverse tastes. Come visit!
hometown: Seattle, Wichita, Boulder, WA, KS, CO
name: Academy of Arts and Sciences

description: Come play with yourself or others, make a new friend or maybe even join in with somebody already playing.  We've got toys to share!
name: Adult Playspace

description: Airships were one of the first crafts built to bring mankind up into the clouds and now Airpusher’s Steampunk Airship is bringing this experience to Burning Man in 2014 with a twist. It's a place for you to dance, laugh, stargaze, and get a breath of fresh air underneath the illuminated balloons of a classic airship. Airpusher presents a new haven for DJs, musicians, aerialists and performance artists alike to showcase their talent on the playa.
name: Airpusher Collective

description: Come join us Wed evening for dusty scientific talks from a Geologist or Botanist or even a guyno talk by our resident Gynecologist. We have the Best Playa Post Card Table to misinform the folks back home where you are.
name: Airstreameri and What Not

description:
Stop by for Bloody Marys or Mimosas at sunrise.  Don't forget your cup!
Feeling in a knot-tying mood? Learn how to make paracord bracelets (everyday in the afternoon) or get hitched. Fake (or real) marriages every sunrise with mimosas.
On Thursday take a swing at the Alot-of-Sacrifice Piñata!  Warning: this piñata is not full of candy.
Cards Against Burning Man! The Massively-Multiplayer-Burning-Man-Themed-Card-Game (MMBMTCG) that you create! (think Apples to Apples/Cards Against Humanity -but Playa style).
name: aLittle

description: A Playanesian Paradise! Get Lei'd and stay for the  conversation!
name: )*(Aloha  =  H'Aloha

description: Aloha and E Komo Mai! Welcome to Aloha Camp! As the migrating Polynesians did long ago using the stars as their navigational tools, we have used the flame in our pu'uwai (hearts) to migrate and lead us to Black Rock City! Come enjoy our island vibes, Aloha Spirit, and Hawaiian culture
name: Aloha Camp

description: The AEZ is a generator free zone. If you like alternative energy, then welcome, you are invited to join our village of friendly folks. You will see and learn about solar panels, wind generators, solar ovens, solar showers, water cleaning, and meet people who can show YOU how to do this.
name: Alternative Energy Zone

description: Are you interested in seeing Burning Man from a different perspective?  Visit Altitude Lounge when you can relax on a couch, meet exciting people, and take in the views from the top of our 42 foot tall tower.  At night we will help you find your way home with our brightly lit navigational beacon.  Our tower is open 24 hours a day and when there are high winds, it is a great escape from blowing gravel.
name: Altitude Lounge

description: AMAZECAMP offers a wonderland chill space underneath a sparkling pyramid. Stroll by on your peaceful nighttime walk through the neighborhood! Pick up some psychedelic glasses to enhance your burning man experience :)
name: AmazeCamp

description: Come wrangle your woes in our hammocks, draw stories on our typewriters, and live to dance about it at the bar. Even amoral stories have morals.
name: Amoral Corral

description: Feeling the heat?  Might as well enjoy it.  M/W/F beer pong and bags (plus some Famous Amos delights), 2-4pm.  Come play with us!
name: Amos

description: Anahasana is a portmanteau of Anahata (Heart Chakra) & Asana (Yogic Body Pose): Heart Embodiment.  We offer classes:  dance, awareness, connection, energy work, meditation, intersubjective meditation, sexual polarity, yoga and acro yoga.  Anahasana Village is a communion of hearts, souls and bodies, holding our light and dark sides in embrace and transparency.
name: Anahasana Village

description: Please come and share the energy of love with our wonderful camp community and enjoy each other. We love meeting people from all over. We will be celebrating Anat’s 20th year attending Burning Man!  She will be dancing & performing at the camp & in the fashion show wearing her many wonderful costumes and she will teach Brazilian Samba dance.
name: Anat's Love Camp

description: Just like religious temples on the Silk Road before us, The Ancient Cult of the Alligator is a resting place for weary travelers before they continue on the Playa Road. The Ancient Cult of the Alligator will offer daily afternoon activities with an open bar providing specialty drinks (Alligator Bites!), music to heal your soul, activities to refresh your mind and body, and a Alligator Deity to unite the community and pay your respects.
name: Ancient Cult of the Alligator

description: Love in all its forms is the constant that binds us together. In our 11th year, ATTOL continues to be the place to love and be loved.  Join us in our famous 24 hour air conditioned Orgy Dome, a consensual sex-positive, inclusionary and exploratory space where couples and moresomes come for unadulterated play.  Relax and make friends in our new Aphrodite’s Garden, attend a class, or enjoy our Thursday night Hot Sex Fire Show.
name: and then there's only LOVE

description: Join us for Cocktails, Culture and Carousing any day between 11am-6pm. Warning: May contain traces of Aussie nuts.
hometown: New York, LA, Seattle, Sydney, Georgia, Buenos Aires, Honolulu, San Fran, Denver, Boston, NY, CA, WA, HI, CO, MA, GA
name: ANITA COCKTAIL

description: We are a 12-step community who co-create a clean and sober environment for like-minded burners to have a safe place to camp. There are meetings from many different fellowships, from sunrise to midnight, and chips to mark years and/or burns. There are nightly excursions to check out the city and/or dance all night. We are not a glum lot.
name: Anonymous Village - AV

description: Anti M’s Home for Wayward Art is a gallery for adopting art; small art, lost art, found art, bad art, original paintings, photography and more.  Come adopt art, take it to a new forever home!
name: Anti M's Home for Wayward Art

description: An interactive sound and visual performance camp.
name: APEX

description: For all things healing, music, poetry, prophecy, and medicine.
name: Dragonfly

description: Celebrations and libations and legendary ski themed party on Wednesday night with old skool tunes. Sample the white wine sangria or experience a shot-ski and frolic with the ski bunnies in the only SNOW on the playa! Wear your gear and goggles and come on up to the north to play! Free chair lift rides and rental ski equipment provided so everyone can shred the playa!
name: Après Ski Black Rock City

description: Kelp Snacks, Mermaids, Monsters.  How many songs do you know about ships?
name: Aquavansary

description: Every caravan through the desert seeks the lush oasis, the secret promise of life-giving Water. The added beauty of Water is that the wisdom you gain can be transmitted to the Water and thereby transmuted to your body. Come quench your thirst at AquaZone's Love Water Bar, once again transmitting Intention to the Water for your body and soul's pleasure.
name: AquaZone

description: Arctica Ice Sales is your center-of-town resource for ice.  Crushed and block ice are available for $3/bag, or a 6-pack of crushed for $15.  During event, ice sales hours are Mon-Sat 9am-6pm, Sun Noon-6pm and 9am-Noon on Labor Day.  Pre-event sales are Thurs-Sun 9am-3pm at this location only.
name: Arctica Ice Sales

description: Ice Cubed is the ice sales igloo located in the 3 o'clock plaza.  Crushed and block ice are available for $3/bag or a 6-pack of crushed for the discounted price of $15.  Ice3 sales hours are Mon-Sat, 9am-6pm and Sun Noon-6pm.
name: Arctica3 Ice Sales - Ice Cubed

description: Ice Nine is the ice sales igloo located in the 9 o'clock plaza.  Crushed and block ice are availalbe for $3 per bag or a 6-pack of crushed at the discounted price of $15.  Ice9 sales hours are Mon-Sat, 9am-6pm, and Sun Noon-6pm.
name: Arctica9 Ice Sales - Ice Nine

description: Bringing spice to the playa.  Come visit us for culinary supplies and surprises 11am-2pm M-Th.
name: Arrakis Spice Market

description: The Arrow Dynamic camp directs you to the here and now.
name: Arrow Dynamic Camp

description: Enter the Sacred Circus for dancing, drinking, sharing, learning, gifting and expressing.  Art Car Bus Stop is a spontaneous autonomous faux municipality.
name: Art Car Bus Stop

description: 2014 is Art Car Camp's 20th year and we'll be celebrating this milestone with a funky used car lot display. We'll be exhibiting both daily drivers (permanently altered, street legal vehicles) and mutants. Art Car Camp is where "Daily Driver" licensed and insured full time art cars are displayed. These are vehicles that work their magic back in the communities from where they hail from all year round. Come see the collection and meet the artists!  Also showing films.
name: Art Car Camp

description: The Art of Such n Such will create an amazing interactive performance/fire performance area for the participants of Black Rock City! Please get involved with our honorarium project "The Infinite Infant and The Trail of Toys! Join us for daily parades, nightly fires, workshops, morning calisthenics, side show, infant care tips & paternity testing. Schedules listed daily!  If you want to get down & do this with us, come on over volunteer, sign up, get involved, be alive, live!
name: ART OF SUCH N SUCH

description: Burning Man's Art Headquarters on Playa
name: ARTery

description: The Grand Hotel at Ashram Galactica - Your Home Away From Home Away From Home
name: Ashram Galactica

description: Asparagus Forest is a chill-out oasis in a sea of sound camps. Visit us to hang out and meet a group of young, open minded individuals or stop by for one of our scheduled activities such as Australia Day, a Pig Roast, Fire Spinning, or Karaoke.
name: Asparagus Forest

description: Good day dirty dwellers! We will be washing hair in the desert again this year. Come visit us with your happy spirits, your smiling faces and your dirty hair and we’ll do our best to make you feel like you’re in heaven. We’ll see you Monday – Friday noon – 4 PM. Remember to arrive early!
name: Astral Headwash

description: We invite all burners to enjoy the night sky with our Star Gazing Pad and experience changing perception with our Box of Perception. Or, you can just chill with us during day and night. On Wednesday and Friday evening, you can join us for hot sake, story telling, and presentation from our residence scientists.
name: Astro Cats

description: Fun, Frisky, n Fabulous! Exploring the PupVerse one lick at a time!
name: AstroPups: Space Station Canis

description: Atlantis is once again reborn.  Join us in the lost city for a taste of the life aquatic, wetter and wilder than ever before.
name: Atlantis

description: The Most Radiant Camp at Burning Man. Come taste our fission ice cream and fusion pancakes. Bounce off the trampoline at the base and enjoy the magnificent view of BRC at the top of our 20’ cooling tower.
name: Atom Cult

description: AudioSpa is a therapeutic sound massage experience.  More at audiospa.org.
name: AudioSpa

description: AutoSub is back for another year of aerials performances,
name: Automatic Subconscious

description: The Avant Yard is home for the Diaspora Arts Collective.  The Diaspora is rapidly expanding as we spread across the planet. We encourage each other to look forward, develop our dreams and experience life to the fullest with an open mind. We want experience life and to encourage others to do the same. We offer Reiki, Meditation, Yoga, Tarot Readings and Massage. And then we hold workshops for these same artforms so that we can spread healing and joy even further.
name: Avant Yard, The

description: We're Awesome!(ville)... that pretty much sums it up.
name: Awesome!(ville)

description: BAAAHS Station is the central depot and homo-licious home on the range to BAAAHS, the Big-Ass Amazingly Awesome Homosexual Sheep - part mutant vehicle, part penetrable sculpture and part rolling disco. Weary travelers come set for a spell, kick up your hooves  and dance or begin a new journey as you slide through a pulsing, pink sphincter into the luscious cocoon of his polyphonic peritoneum.
name: BAAAHS Station

description: The Bacon Oasis offers amber jewels of deliciously sticky bacon for early risers and dusty returners.
name: Bacon Oasis

description: You've done some pretty stupid shit at burning man -- we want to hear your fantastically bad advice for virgin burners. Like the worst. Think you got what it takes to impress us with your follies?
name: Bad Advice Wanted

description: BADLANDS funk jams! Come and join us on the front porch and put a little bit of chicken grease on your ankle bone to get you shaking proper on the playa!
name: BADLANDS

description: Experience Burning Man baggage free!  Check your baggage with us---emotional baggage only!---by writing it in our book, which we will burn at the Temple Burn.
name: Baggage Check

description: "To be confused or thrown off thoroughly and completely" yeah, that's about right. We are your dirty dirty bar in the desert striving for radial self stupidity. Come endure our special shots and ride our giant steel rocking horse "Ruckus". You'll stop for a minute, but stay for hours.
name: BAMBOOZLED!

description: Bandan-Aroma offers  participants the opportunity to infuse aromatic oils onto handcrafted bandanas to keep and  wear as fashionable yet practical accessories as they caravan about the Playa, protecting against dust storms and providing a more pleasant experience when visiting the porta-potties. The Bandana Brigade is a caravanning band of bandana-wearing Bandan-Aroma  campmates on bikes (tongue twister!), who will make surprise visits to randomly selected porta-potty banks, offering bandanas and essential oil application to Burners congregated outside.
name: Bandan-Aroma and Bandana Brigade

description: Explore purifying and bonding experience of traditional Russian sauna: dry and steam heat with birch twig lashings
name: Banya Camp

description: Bao Chicka Wow Wow will be serving steamed pork buns and hot tea.
name: Bao Chicka Wow Wow

description: It’s three days into the Burn and you’re already cursing that tangled mess that used to be your hair. Come get it trimmed, cut, or just plain buzzed at Barber Ella Shop, the interplanetary playa salon that wants to give you a mohawk while surrounding you with sexy sci-fi impersonators. Hey, are you a haircutting pro? We always have chairs and equipment open for guest stylists. Bzzzz.
name: Barber Ella Shop

description: Barbie Day Spa.... best damned day spa on the playa... stop by and get pampered.  Massage, body wash, fingernail painting, and wine.
name: Barbie Day Spa

description: Come on in to BDC&WB- enjoy fine fine from a cheap paper cup in our climate controlled Bistro while you tickle the ivories or your neighbor. Marvel at our sick and twisted art displays and make memories to last a lifetime or a at least a few precious moments.
name: Barbie Death Camp

description: Back again for another triumphant year on the playa, Barbie Death Village and it's subcamps (Barbie Death Camp & Wine Bistro, Barbie Day Spa, Barbie Boutique, Dye With Dignity, Dread Pirate Barbie, Black Rock City Body & Paint, Clan O'Crash, Meercats, Ohio Boyz, and Loose Nutz) will be there to welcome all burners.  Feel free to drop on by for a nice glass of wine or Otter Pop and get a load of the sickest bastards on the playa.
name: Barbie Death Village

description: Calling all athletes, enginerds, beach bums and kids-at-heart: saunter or stumble over to the Barbot playground, where Cyborg Volterra oversees old-school yard games to get you smiling. Quench your thirst on Tuesday or Thursday afternoon with Moscow Mules at the happiest of Russian-themed happy hours, served by Volterra, our robotic bartender who mixes ‘em up stiff!
name: Barbots of Santa Barbarikon

description: Cold coffee and beautiful baristas. We provide a nice pick-me-up, in more ways than one.
name: Barechested Baristas

description: Welcome to Basshenge! Stop on down to the 2 side and come rock that body!!. Beats bumping from 9pm to 9am. Fire, Performers, Circus Acts, Step right up folks its time to PARTY!!!
name: Basshenge

description: The Bat Carnival- We are the spine-tingling fright of the funhouse mixed with the thrill of carnival games of chance. Our camp is one part motley stable of stick ponies and one part ooky-spooky carnival.
name: Bat Carnival

description: Battle Born Burners where "Welcome Home Means Nevada" is our mantra. Join the freaks from the desert on the desert to get your "Nevadatude" on, with those of us who count the days, till our blessed "burn time".
name: Battle Born Burners

description: The B.C. (British Columbia) Village brings together different camps hailing from various regions of British Columbia, Canada. Come party like a Canuck: enjoy uniquely Canadian drinks, bike and art cars, and a homage to Canadian astronaught Chris Hadfield.
name: BC Village

description: stop by, you will like us
name: Be There Now
Beach @ the End of the Universe

description: Once again the mighty BEARWHALE saunters forth from Kamchatka in search of migratory cucumbers, elk fairy dust, and playa shenanigans.  Stop by to bask in the glow of this evolutionary marvel!
name: Bearwhalea

description: This camp is devoted to turning your energy UP!! We will have Beats Droppin, Booze Flowin and a Boutique to enhance your style on the playa! Our positive and loving vybes will make your stay at our camp EPYK!
name: Beats Boutique

description: Camp Beaverton is an intentional, experimental, and experiential Burning Man community theme camp. Our goal is to provide a safe space for queer women on and off-Playa. We encourage education, participation, inquiry, conversation, and self-reflection on what it means to be “a Beaver” AND extend our goals to the greater Black Rock community by hosting workshops and social events.
name: Beaverton
